// The `prelude.file` sub-module: read a `file` value's content and metadata in-runtime. A `file` is a
// slim handle into the project's blob store — the value carries only the reference (identity); the
// bytes AND the metadata stay runtime-side, so programs pass files around for free and nothing on the
// handle can go stale or be forged. These primitives are the bridge for the moments content or
// metadata must be read, e.g. base64 for a multimodal model's `inline_data` part.

@"The file's bytes, base64-encoded — the inline shape multimodal model APIs take. The whole content
materialises as one string, so mind the size (a large file makes a large request body)."
primitive agent read_base64(value: file) -> string

@"The file's recorded MIME type (e.g. \"image/png\"), read from the project's file catalog; \"\" when
none was recorded at upload."
primitive agent content_type(value: file) -> string

@"The file's size in bytes, read from the project's file catalog (no content download)."
primitive agent size(value: file) -> integer
